Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index rose 0.9 percent to 7,706.26. The
gauge fell 2.9 percent this week.  KGI Securities Co. (6008)  (6008 TT), the nationâ€™s second-largest
brokerage, gained 6.6 percent to NT$12.15, the steepest increase
since Jan. 30.  China Development Financial Holding Corp. (2883)  (2883
TT) offered to buy all of KGI Securities for as much as NT$54.6
billion in cash and stock. It offered NT$5.5 in cash and 1.2 of
its own shares for each share of KGI Securities, valuing the
transaction at NT$16.71 per share, China Development said in an
exchange filing. China Development advanced 4.7 percent to
NT$8.74, the most since Feb. 3.  TPK Holding Co. (3673)  (3673 TT), a maker of touch panels, rose 5
percent to NT$449, the most since Feb. 15. The company reported
an increase in first-quarter sales.  To contact the reporters on this story:
